node.title: Almost 50 police officers barred from work as WA COVID-19 vaccination mandate enforced
node.description: The officers are among tens of thousands of Western Australians who are required to have had one dose of a vaccine by today.

node.title: Defence backflips to produce evidence of seaman's bullying before suicide
node.description: Defence backflipped on being able to find documents relating to the bullying of a suicidal young seaman only after the royal commission into veteran suicide began, the seaman's sister reveals.

node.title: SA records first cases of community transmission since state borders reopened
node.description: South Australia has recorded three new cases of COVID-19, including the first instances of apparent community transmission since borders reopened last week.

node.title: Tucson Moves to Fire Officer Seen Fatally Shooting Man in Wheelchair
node.description: A man who was said to have stolen a toolbox from a Walmart and flashed a knife at an employee was shot nine shots in the back and side in a confrontation captured on video, the police said.

node.title: Preliminary Injunction Blocks Biden's Federal Vaccine Mandate in Kentucky, Ohio, Tennessee
node.description: The blocking of the mandate for federal contractors in three states joined the series of current legal challenges to President Joe Biden's vaccine mandates.

node.title: MBIE officials meet with Auckland Council over delays to hospital building consents
node.description: Consents for medical facilities are being held up by extra questions about fire safety designs.

node.title: Covid-19 update: 146 new community cases today
node.description: There are 146 new community cases of Covid-19 in New Zealand today, with 83 people in hospital.

node.title: Gun used in Michigan school shooting was purchased by suspect’s father.
node.description: The semiautomatic gun used in the shooting at Oxford high school was purchased by the suspect’s father on Nov. 26, four days before Tuesday’s shooting.

node.title: Oregon Working to Join States That Offer Electronic Vaccine Verification Tool
node.description: Oregon is looking to join the nine states that provide digital proof of COVID vaccination to its residents with a program set to release in the spring.

node.title: Nevada's Boxing Commission Says Charity Event Where Student Was Killed Was Not Licensed
node.description: Nathan Tyler Valencia, 20, died Nov. 23 from blunt force head trauma, the Clark County coroner's office said, after partaking in a charity boxing event.

node.title: In Light of World AIDS Day, CDC Reports HIV Rate Remains Severe Among Gay, Bisexual Men
node.description: While HIV infections among gay and bisexual men decreased 8 percent over the last decade, gay and bi men still accounted for 66 percent of all new HIV infections in 2019.

node.title: What are the key takeaways from the review into parliament's work culture?
node.description: Yesterday's report into the culture of work in federal parliament, sparked by Brittany Higgins's allegations, painted a pretty sobering picture. These are the key recommendations for how to make Parliament House a better place to work.

node.title: Alex, 84, is being evicted from his home after the collapse of a housing scheme
node.description: As a Senate inquiry looks into the collapse of the Sterling Group housing scheme, some of the elderly victims are now finding themselves homeless.

node.title: Victorian government dismisses 'blackmail' claims from Djokovic's dad over Aus Open vaccine mandate
node.description: Victorian Sports Minister Martin Pakula rejects claims by Novak Djokovic's dad that Australian Open organisers are forcing players to get vaccinated against COVID-19.

node.title: Space junk has forced NASA to temporarily postpone a spacewalk. So where did it come from?
node.description: NASA is forced to temporarily postpone a spacewalk because of space junk that could puncture an astronaut's suit or damage the International Space Station.

node.title: Andre Dickens, a Veteran City Council Member, Is Elected Mayor of Atlanta
node.description: Mr. Dickens and Felicia Moore had advanced to the runoff election by beating former Mayor Kasim Reed.

node.title: Mother Charged With Stabbing 3-Month-Old Son to Death, Then Discarding Him in a Dumpster
node.description: Fardoussa Abdillahi, 26, has been charged with second-degree murder Tuesday. She could be sentenced to up to 40 years in prison if convicted.

node.title: Rule options now available for community rugby
node.description: World Rugby will allow community teams to use 10 players, play shorter matches and change the size of the ball as part of flexible new rules.

node.title: 'We don't want them walking the streets': Morcombe family welcomes tougher child killer parole laws
node.description: State Parliament last night passed amendments to the Corrective Services Act which could see the "worst of the worst" kept behind bars for decades after their parole date.

node.title: Backpacker tells inquest Theo Hayez didn't appear drunk on the night he disappeared in Byron Bay
node.description: Inquest hears the missing backpacker was sober enough to talk about European politics before Google searching a small village seldom known to tourists.

node.title: China's trade war was intended to bring Australia 'to its knees'. A top US adviser says Canberra may have won
node.description: US President Joe Biden's top Asia adviser says that China's campaign of economic punishment against Australia has failed, predicting that Beijing will re-engage over time on Australia's terms.

node.title: Everything we know about the Omicron cases in NSW right now
node.description: Three flights into Sydney in recent days have been carrying passengers infected with the new COVID-19 Omicron variant — here's a breakdown of what we know so far.

node.title: Covid-19: Hospitalisation rate has dropped, Bloomfield says
node.description: New modelling shows hospitalisation and ICU bed usage has levelled off in Auckland, the Director-General of Health says.

node.title: Haast's Eagle research points to bird being carnivorous predator
node.description: The largest eagle in the world, which resided in New Zealand, may have been bald and a carnivorous predator, according to new research.

node.title: LeBron James Enters NBA Health Protocols as Recent Tumultuous Stretch Continues
node.description: James was suspended and fined before Tuesday's news he would miss a stretch of games, making the last week one of the strangest in his epic career.

node.title: Former Theranos CEO Holmes Spends Another Emotional Day in Court Centered on Her Ex-Lover
node.description: Elizabeth Holmes, 37, cried as she was asked by a federal prosecutor to read aloud some of the texts exchanged between her and Ramesh "Sunny" Balwani, 56.

node.title: Teens have easier access to drugs as illegal trade booms on social media
node.description: Drug dealers are leveraging social media to reach teenagers.

node.title: Investigator Cites Video and Other Evidence Against Jussie Smollett
node.description: A detective told jurors at Mr. Smollett’s trial how the actor had gone from victim to suspect as the investigation unfolded. But the actor’s lawyer suggested the police work was not thorough.

node.title: Teen Allegedly Shot Another at School After Seeing Money Received in Gun Sale Was Fake
node.description: The 15-year-old is facing charges of endangerment, aggravated assault, and weapons violations relating to bringing a weapon on campus.

node.title: Officer Who Shot and Killed Pharrell Williams' Cousin Cleared of Charges By Grand Jury
node.description: Solomon Simmons, a Black Virginia Beach police officer, shot and killed Donovan Lynch after he saw Lynch with a gun near a crowded parking lot.
